The paper deals with the problem of testing identity against a given distribution, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and has applications in various areas such as data science (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and statistics (cs.SI). The paper also mentions that the techniques used in their analysis may be useful for other distribution testing problems, which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
